external_knowledge:
- High-performing articles refers to articles with engagement scores lower than the user's average engagement score; 
- Seasoned web users are users who have a preferred environment ID of 0; 
- Consistently engage more than the average article viewer means the user's average engagement score is higher than the article's average engagement score; 
- Browsed over 100 times refers to users who have a total click count greater than 100.

sql:
SELECT article_id, total_clicks, AVG(average_session_duration) AS average_session_duration, click_through_rate
FROM content_performance
GROUP BY article_id, total_clicks, click_through_rate;
